i(w) is the proportion of words found at position i that are equal to w. Thus, positions with low k-mer sequence diversity—e.g., only one or two unique words occurring throughout the alignment at that position—will have low entropy, while positions that have high sequence diversity will have high entropy. We included only the ungapped words in the entropy calculation and introduce a uniform gap penalty to disfavor gapped positions in our calculation.

